{
  "doc_id": "31105",
  "text": "Robust expression of both DUX4fl mRNA and protein is seen in normal testis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] where it may have a role in germ cell maintenance and development [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Endogenous expression of these stable DUX4fl transcripts in testis probably does not depend on the FSHD-associated PAS as they appear to utilize different, downstream pA signals [CITATION_5] . As a quarter of Europeans are homozygous for the 4qB allele and therefore lack the FSHDassociated PAS [CITATION_6] , it is probably not essential for normal DUX4 transcription.",
